<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Privacy Policy - Card Strategy 21</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Privacy Policy for Card Strategy 21" />
  <style>
    :root {
      --bg: #0f1217;
      --panel: #171b22;
      --text: #eef2f7;
      --muted: #b8c1cc;
      --accent: #ffd166;
      --line: #2b3340;
    }
    * { box-sizing: border-box; }
    body {
      margin: 0;
      font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;
      background: var(--bg);
      color: var(--text);
      line-height: 1.7;
    }
    .wrap {
      max-width: 920px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 32px 20px 64px;
    }
    .card {
      background: var(--panel);
      border: 1px solid var(--line);
      border-radius: 18px;
      padding: 28px;
      box-shadow: 0 12px 30px rgba(0,0,0,.25);
    }
    h1, h2 { line-height: 1.25; }
    h1 {
      margin: 0 0 8px;
      color: var(--accent);
      font-size: 2rem;
    }
    h2 {
      margin-top: 28px;
      margin-bottom: 10px;
      font-size: 1.15rem;
    }
    p, li {
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: 1rem;
    }
    a { color: var(--accent); }
    .meta {
      margin-bottom: 22px;
      color: var(--muted);
      font-size: .95rem;
    }
    .note {
      border-left: 4px solid var(--accent);
      padding: 10px 14px;
      background: rgba(255, 209, 102, 0.08);
      border-radius: 10px;
      margin: 18px 0 8px;
    }
    ul { padding-left: 22px; }
    code {
      background: #0a0d12;
      padding: 2px 6px;
      border-radius: 6px;
      color: #fff;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>
  <div class="wrap">
    <div class="card">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <div class="meta">
        App: <strong>Card Strategy 21</strong><br />
        Developer: <strong>MM Lucky Team</strong><br />
        Effective date: <strong>March 15, 2026</strong>
      </div>

      <p>
        This Privacy Policy explains how Card Strategy 21 (“the App”) handles user and device data.
        By using the App, you agree to the practices described in this Privacy Policy.
      </p>

      <div class="note">
        This App is a single-player simulated card strategy game. It does not provide real-money gambling,
        cash-out features, or prizes with real-world monetary value.
      </div>

      <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
      <p>
        We do not require you to create an account, and we do not directly collect personal information such as your
        name, phone number, postal address, or government identification.
      </p>
      <p>
        The App may process limited device and usage data through third-party services used to support advertising,
        app performance, and security. This may include:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Advertising identifiers</li>
        <li>Device information such as device model, operating system, and language settings</li>
        <li>App interaction data, diagnostics, crash logs, and performance data</li>
        <li>Approximate location inferred from IP address by advertising or analytics providers</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        The App may also store game-related preferences locally on your device, such as sound settings,
        gameplay progress, or non-monetary in-game statistics.
      </p>

      <h2>2. How We Use Information</h2>
      <p>We and our service providers may use information to:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Display ads in the App</li>
        <li>Measure ad performance and prevent invalid traffic or fraud</li>
        <li>Maintain app security, stability, and performance</li>
        <li>Fix bugs and improve gameplay experience</li>
        <li>Store local preferences and restore basic game settings</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Third-Party Services</h2>
      <p>
        The App may use third-party SDKs or services, including Google AdMob, to display advertisements and support
        app operations. These providers may collect, use, or share certain data under their own privacy policies.
      </p>
      <p>
        Example third-party service:
        <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Privacy Policy</a>
      </p>

      <h2>4. Data Sharing</h2>
      <p>
        We do not sell your personal information. However, limited data may be shared with third-party service
        providers only as necessary for advertising, analytics, diagnostics, security, and app functionality.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Data Storage and Retention</h2>
      <p>
        Some gameplay preferences and progress may be stored locally on your device. Data processed by third-party
        services is retained according to those providers’ own retention practices and legal obligations.
      </p>
      <p>
        We retain data only as long as reasonably necessary for the purposes described in this Privacy Policy,
        to comply with legal obligations, or to resolve disputes and enforce agreements.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Data Deletion</h2>
      <p>
        Because the App does not require account creation, there is generally no account-based personal profile for us
        to delete. You can remove locally stored gameplay data by clearing the App’s storage or uninstalling the App
        from your device.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you contact us with a privacy request, we will review it and respond within a reasonable time, subject to
        applicable law and our technical capabilities.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Children’s Privacy</h2>
      <p>
        The App is not directed to children under the age threshold required by applicable law in the regions where
        the App is distributed, unless explicitly stated otherwise in the store listing and app settings.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you believe a child has provided personal information in connection with the App, please contact us so that
        we can review the situation and take appropriate action.
      </p>

      <h2>8. Security</h2>
      <p>
        We take reasonable measures to protect information handled through the App. However, no method of electronic
        storage or transmission is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
      </p>

      <h2>9. International Data Processing</h2>
      <p>
        Third-party services used by the App may process data on servers located outside your country. By using the
        App, you understand that data may be processed in other jurisdictions, subject to applicable safeguards.
      </p>

      <h2>10. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any updates will be posted on this page with a revised
        effective date.
      </p>

      <h2>11. Contact Us</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions or requests about this Privacy Policy, contact:<br />
        <strong>MM Lucky Team</strong><br />
        Email: <strong>mmluckyteam@gmail.com</strong>
      </p>

      <h2>12. Important Notes for Store Compliance</h2>
      <p>
        You should make sure your Google Play Data safety form matches the actual behavior of your App,
        SDKs, permissions, and this Privacy Policy.
      </p>
      <p>
        If you add account creation, cloud save, login, analytics, payments, location access, contacts,
        microphone, camera, or any new SDKs in the future, you should update this Privacy Policy before publishing
        the update.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
